5. Hierarchical “Shadow” Chunking Strategy 
This design balances precision, context, and safety. 
5.1 Three-Level Hierarchy 
Level 1 — Atomic Chunks (128–256 tokens) 
• Optimized for high-precision semantic retrieval 
• Stored in the Vector DB 
Level 2 — Clinical Context Chunks (512–768 tokens) 
• Parent context (dosage, contraindications, evidence level) 
• Stored in SQL / document store 
Level 3 — Full Document 
• Used only for: 
o Final synthesis 
o Long-form summarization 
o Audits 
5.2 Context Injection (Critical) 
Every Atomic Chunk is transformed before embedding: 
[DOC_TITLE]: ... 
[SECTION]: ... 
[SOURCE_TIER]: ... 
[EVIDENCE_LEVEL]: ... 
[CONTENT]: 
... 
This guarantees that even small chunks carry medical meaning in isolation. 
6. Embedding & Index Isolation 
6.1 Embedding Rules 
• A single, consistent embedding model is used 
• No mixing of models within an index 
• Re-embedding always requires a full index rebuild 
6.2 Domain-Isolated Indices 
Separate vector indices prevent semantic collisions: 
• clinical_guidelines_index 
• clinical_trials_index 
• lifestyle_health_index 
• user_uploaded_index 
Routing happens before retrieval, not after. 
7. Hybrid Retrieval Architecture 
7.1 Vector Index (Semantic Reasoning) 
• Handles nuance, similarity, explanations 
• Uses metadata pre-filtering: 
o Tier 
o Recency 
o Evidence type 
7.2 Knowledge Graph (Hard Medical Logic) 
A parallel Knowledge Graph (KG) stores: 
• Drug → Drug interactions 
• Drug → Condition contraindications 
• Trial phase → Evidence strength 
Override Rule: 
If KG detects a contraindication, it overrides vector retrieval results, regardless of semantic 
similarity. 
7.3 Temporal & Evidence Filters 
Queries can enforce: 
• “Only RCTs” 
• “Only studies from last N months” 
• “Exclude Phase 1 trials” 
8. Medical Safety Gates & Conflict Engine 
8.1 Contradiction Detection 
• Top-K retrieved chunks are cross-checked 
• If conflicts are detected (e.g., dosage mismatch): 
o A Contradiction Cluster is formed 
o The system: 
▪ Flags uncertainty 
▪ Produces a hedged response 
▪ Escalates when risk is high 
8.2 Trial Phase Handling 
• Phase 1 trials → downgraded 
• Phase 4 / approved drugs → promoted 
• Trial phase directly affects authority weighting 
9. Query-Time Safety & Auditability 
9.1 Query Intent Classifier 
Every query is classified as: 
• Emergency / Diagnostic 
• General research 
• Educational 
Emergency intents trigger: 
• Immediate disclaimers 
• Redirection to medical professionals 
• Suppression of actionable advice 
9.2 Full Audit Trail 
Every answer stores: 
• Query 
• Retrieved chunk_ids 
• Source document version hashes 
• Authority scores 
• Conflict flags 
• Reviewer or system decision ID 
This enables: 
• Debugging 
• Legal traceability 
• Regulatory audits 
9.3 Blue/Green Index Deployment 
• New data is ingested into a Shadow Index 
• Validation suite is run: 
o Golden questions 
o Recall checks 
o Noise audits 
• Only then is the live pointer switched 
Zero downtime, zero silent regressions. 
